\pard\ql\b\fs28 Abstract\par
\b0\fs24
MediFlow is a web-based Hospital Management System that helps patients, doctors, and administrators manage appointments, patient queues, and medical records. The system provides role-based dashboards, secure login using JSON Web Tokens (JWT), and real-time queue updates using Socket.IO. The frontend is built with Next.js (React + TypeScript) and Tailwind CSS, and the backend is built with Node.js and Express. MongoDB is used for storing users, appointments, queue entries, and medical records. This report describes the background, design, implementation, and testing of the system in simple and clear terms.\par
